GB men claim Euro Indoor relay gold
However, there was disappointment for 800m runner <Name>Jenny Meadows</Name>, who finished fourth in her final in a time of 2:01.52.
She led after three laps but faded badly and was overtaken in the final 200m as Ukraine's <Name>Nataliya Lupu</Name> won the gold medal in 2:00.26.
<Name>Meadows</Name> was the defending champion, having had her silver medal from Paris in 2011 upgraded when Russian athlete <Name>Yevgeniya Zinurova</Name> failed a drugs test.
